   10 Sep 2013

We must do more to save children from scourge of conflict says UN envoy

   Listen /

   The park's playground teems with newly arrived Syrian refugee children.
   UNHCR/S. Baldwin

   As the war in Syria continues unabated, children continue to bear the
   brunt of the conflict, says the Secretary-General's Special
   Representative for Children and Armed Conflict.

   Leila Zerrougi, on a recent visit to Syria, met with many children and
   their families who expressed the horrors of the conflict, their fears
   and their preoccupation for their children's loss of education.

   Beng Poblete-Enriquez has the story.

   Duration: 3'12''


